<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c29c25d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2106"><num value="2106">§ 2106.</num><heading> Savings clauses</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c29c25e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2106/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Tennessee Valley Authority jurisdiction</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed as replacing or superseding <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s831y–1">section 831y–1 of title 16</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c29c25f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2106/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> State jurisdiction</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed as extending or diminishing the jurisdiction or authority of any State over the siting, construction, monitoring, or managing of artificial reefs within its boundaries.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6c29c260-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/623/tII/s208">Pub. L. 98–623, title II, § 208</ref>, <date date="1984-11-08">Nov. 8, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/3398">98 Stat. 3398</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
